Where Author Jacqueline Woodson Would Like To Take Young People's Literature In 2018The National Ambassador for Young People's Literature, Gene Luen Yang passed the baton to his successor Jacqueline Woodson on Tuesday.
KELLY MCEVERS, HOST:At the Library of Congress today, Gene Luen Yang officially ended his tenure as national ambassador for young people's literature and handed the baton to Jacqueline Woodson.
NEARY: As she takes on the job, Jacqueline Woodson has no illusions about the perks.
JACQUELINE WOODSON: My hope is that by that time I'm no longer national ambassador I'll have changed the world.
NEARY: Like her predecessors, Jacqueline Woodson will be traveling all over the country to meet with young people.